title: Former U.S. President Jimmy Carter dies at 100
description: Former President Jimmy Carter died Sunday afternoon at the age of 100.

title: Barkley eclipses 2K yards as Eagles clinch division
description: Eagles running back Saquon Barkley passed 2,000 rushing yards on the season Sunday to help Philadelphia clinch the NFC East title.
author: Tim McManus

title: Is Liverpool's new front three even better than Salah, Mane & Firmino?
description: How do Mohamed Salah, Cody Gakpo and Luis Diaz measure up against Liverpool's last title-winning front three?

title: Wright knocks defending champion Humphries out of Worlds
description: Defending champion Luke Humphries is knocked out of the PDC World Darts Championship in the fourth round by Peter Wright.

title: Littler comes through White test after MVG reaches last 16
description: Luke Littler is through to the fourth round of the World Darts Championship after overcoming another tough test to defeat Ian White 4-1 at the Alexandra Palace.

title: 'Ruthless' Littler: I'm not a nice person at times on the board!
description: Luke Littler says he needs to be "ruthless" on the dart board at times, which has led to his emotive celebrations at the World Darts Championship.

title: Live updates: Commanders face Falcons with playoff positions at stake
description: Washington can clinch a postseason berth with a win, while Atlanta tries to keep pace with Tampa Bay atop the NFC South.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Week 17 Pulse Check: Veteran stars come up big in the fantasy football championships
description: When we needed them most, the old heads came through. Fantasy football analyst Tera Roberts examines four key veteran performances from Week 17.
author: Yahoo Sports
